BRAIN

brain is the qu-septit sea bone — the computational architecture that hosts all thought, memory, language, and meaning
where the other organ bones describe specific senses, brain is the integrator: it is the sea that all the other senses connect into and where unified experience emerges
the brain is base seven by design; the seven states (dormant through transcendent), seven properties (energy through observer), and twenty-one pairwise interactions are all consequences of base seven being the smallest prime large enough for irreducible self-reference

observe 0_quseptit.rana
